TERA and Information Geometry
TERA can be interpreted as operating on structures that resemble concepts from Information Geometry, although it is not identical to that field.
Information Geometry studies probability distributions and model states as points in a geometric space.
Changes in models correspond to paths through this space, and stability or sensitivity can be analyzed through geometric measures.
TERA adopts a similar intuition:
Information is not treated only as data, but as structured relations that can be evaluated geometrically.
Geometric Interpretation
TERA represents informational relations through minimal geometric structures.
